name: Year Of The Tiger
description:
Celebrating Chinese New Year 2022. WAGMI 

The Chinese Zodiac, a system that has existed in Chinese culture for more than 2,000 years, dictates which animal represents a given year.

The cycle repeats every 12 years, and 2022 is the Year of the Tiger.

Different characteristics are assigned to each animal, and this is traditionally used to determine fortune. The animals are also thought to represent the personalities of people born that year.

The tiger is associated with power, rebellion, adventure and unpredictability.
